<br>
So here's a question for you.  The general concept behind a paladin's powers is that the come from his/her deity.  My question is, does a paladin get them all at once, and have to learn and practice how to use them, or does his deity grant a little at a time, and the paladin has to prove himself worthy to be given more?<br>
<br>
One could make an argument for either case, or even argue that there's no difference, really between the two: that the deity grants as much power as the paladin can handle.  When the paladin realizes he can handle more, or needs more, he has more.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure 100% where I stand on this issue myself, but I'm writing a short story with two paladin characters:  one would be a fairly low-level paladin, and the other would be a totally untrained paladin.  In fact, he's unaware he really is a paladin:  he just does things, sometimes, that seem amazing.<br>
<br>
Let me know what you all think, por favor.<br>
<br>
